## **Dark Mode Support**

### **Automatic Dark Mode**
The theme automatically supports dark mode through CSS custom properties. Components should use semantic color classes:

```tsx
// ✅ DO: Use semantic colors that adapt to dark mode
<div className="bg-background text-foreground border-border">
  <h2 className="text-card-foreground">Title</h2>
  <p className="text-muted-foreground">Description</p>
</div>
```

## **Implementation Checklist**

When creating or modifying UI components:

- [ ] **Colors**: Use semantic color classes (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, etc.)
- [ ] **Typography**: Use semantic typography classes (`text-h1`, `text-body`, etc.)
- [ ] **Spacing**: Use semantic spacing classes (`space-section`, `space-component`)
- [ ] **Shadows**: Use semantic shadow classes (`shadow-modern`, `shadow-lg`)
- [ ] **Borders**: Use semantic border classes (`border-border`, `border-modern`)
- [ ] **Focus**: Include `focus-modern` for interactive elements
- [ ] **Hover**: Include `hover-modern` or `hover-modern-subtle` for interactive elements
- [ ] **Accessibility**: Include `sr-only` for screen reader content
- [ ] **Dark Mode**: Ensure colors work in both light and dark modes
- [ ] **Consistency**: Follow the established design patterns

